passages.text: Reiterate Rating: BUY | PO: 167.00 USD | Price: 134.05 USD

We remain bullish on shares of DELL where we expect long term EPS growth of \(15\%\) over the next five years (see our 18 July note) supported by strong growth in Al servers. The qtr and FY guide re-affirmed our confidence in Dell continuing to drive upside to Al server consensus rev ests. Dell also delivered \(\) 2.5bn\(in operating cash flow while growing ISG revs by\) 44\% \(driven by strong Al server performance). Shares of DELL are trading at 12x C26E EPS and 9x P/FCF and 11x EV/uFCF, which we view as attractive given the rev and EPS growth profile. Reit. Buy as we are still in the early stages of Al adoption, margins from mix, and tailwind from upcoming PC refresh and longer-term Al PC adoption.

Dell exceeded Al server rev expectations and guide in F2Q, (\\$8.2bn vs guide \(\) 7bn). As a result of the beat and ongoing robust demand, Dell raised Al server revs \(+\) 5bn to \(\) 20bn\(for F26E weighted slightly more to F3Q. Importantly, mgmt. guided Al server margins to grow in the 2H as enterprise and sovereign customers continue to grow in mix (+DD% q/q growth in F2Q). We model F3Q Al server revs of\) \ \(6.1bn\) (Fig 1) and F26E of \(\) 21.8bn\(and there could be upside to\) \ \(25bn\) by the end of the year. While Al servers remain margin dilutive to the total company in the n-t, Dell expects profitability to improve as revs scale and enterprise and sovereign customer mix grows.

Dell expects better 2H than 1H for PCs, ISS, & StorageDell expects an improved 2H compared to 1H in CSG, ISS, and Storage which will be boosted by Win10 EOL in October, higher server content/configs, and more Dell IP in storage. Dell estimates \(- 50\%\) of the PC installed base has upgraded already to Win11 which leaves a significant opportunity to drive CSG revs in 2H vs 1H and mgmt. noted PC refresh momentum will continue into C26. In Storage, Dell expects better seq 2H performance driven by more Dell IP and a seasonal acceleration in 4Q.
Our F26E rev/EPs move to \(\) 108.5bn/\(\) 9.64\(from\) \ \(106.9bn/\) 9.48. Our PO moves to \(\) 167\(from\) \ \(165\) on 15x (unchanged) our C26E EPS of \(\) 11.13\(prior\) \ \(11.04\)

Our PO of \(\) 167\(is based on approximately 15x our C26E EPS estimate of\) \ \(11.13\) . Our target multiple compares to median 5x of historical range 3x- 18x for Dell since it returned to the public markets in 2019. Dell went private in 2013 and prior to that the company had a very different structure. As such, we do not believe earlier historical trading multiples are meaningful. In our opinion, a multiple higher than the historical range is warranted given favorable exposure to Al (across servers, storage and PCs), improved storage portfolio, lower financial leverage and it balances opportunities to invest in core areas of growth, with ongoing weak macro.

Downside risks: faster- than- expected slowdown in the global economy, which could prove to be a headwind to revenue growth, faster- than- expected strengthening of the U.S. dollar, trade war with China, and higher- than- expected tariffs, Dell not being able to source needed processors from Intel, and unexpected share loss to competitors.

Upside risks: faster- than- expected revenue growth and market share gain, faster mix shift to storage and premium PC and server configurations, which can drive upside to margins, faster- than- expected ramp of sales teams, and adoption of Al that can drive upside to cash flow across PCs and servers (negative cash conversion cycle).
